about: Hi there, my name is Michelle Wong and this is my website! I am a fresh graduate from the University of Toronto with my degree being in Computer Science and Mathematics. During my time at UofT, I've had the opportunity to be a TA for second year theory courses (CSC236) and more practical ones (CSC209, CSC384). My hobbies include mahjong, rhythm games, and dancing. You can contact me at: chellewsa@gmail.com

project_list.name: React Website
project_list.desc: I made this website in React! It was something I wanted to try doing for a while ever since my first website I created years ago using purely HTML and CSS.

project_list.name: Discord Bot
project_list.desc: I made this bot for my academic society. It was used to help out with courses and shuttle bus routes.

project_list.name: Filename Scrambler
project_list.desc: Small little bash script I wrote to help manage my background images.

project_list.name: DDR Recorder
project_list.desc: I made this sideproject for my passion at DDR. I always wanted a way to collect my scores in an easy format. The idea to add ML to it so that photos can help with info taking was a problem I experienced at the end of any of my sessions. I would be so tired afterwards haha
